ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would recommend this course to someone interested in developmental psychology.
A great way to learn about the last couple of decades of infant and related research, would recommend.
I would say that they will learn, but that class time at times can lull a bit
I would definetely recommend the class to get a rough overview of infant studies.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: This class is really not related to what I research on--even though we read about object/visual perception in infants, the papers were not about new effects. Otherwise, it helped me discipline my creative thinking (esp. the homework assignments).
